🎶Offering Free VIRTUAL Voice & Acting Lessons!🎶

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a music theatre voice teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are proud to have a team of dedicated and experienced teachers who are passionate about helping students discover the joy of music. 

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, acting, violin, viola, cello, and guitar, along with 2 in person recitals each year in MI, WI, IL, and MO. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you’re preparing for auditions, looking to grow as a performer, or simply want to enjoy making music, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

Try a free lesson today! This is a great way to meet one of our teachers, experience a lesson, and see how music can be a fun and meaningful part of your life.

If you’d like to get started, fill out this form, and we’ll match you with the teacher who’s the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

🎶Offering Free VIRTUAL Voice & Acting Lessons!🎶

Hi! I'm Colleen and I'm a music theatre voice teacher, and the owner of Virtuoso Studios. We are proud to have a team of dedicated and experienced teachers who are passionate about helping students discover the joy of music. 

We currently offer lessons in voice, piano, acting, violin, viola, cello, and guitar, along with 2 in person recitals each year in MI, WI, IL, and MO. Each of our teachers is committed to providing personalized instruction to help every student reach their goals. Whether you’re preparing for auditions, looking to grow as a performer, or simply want to enjoy making music, our teachers are here to support and encourage you every step of the way!

Try a free lesson today! This is a great way to meet one of our teachers, experience a lesson, and see how music can be a fun and meaningful part of your life.

If you’d like to get started, fill out this form, and we’ll match you with the teacher who’s the best fit for your goals and interests. [www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons](https://www.virtuosostudios.org/free-trial-lessons)

sharedPost.text:
🌀🌀🎥🏆Highly advanced acting course on.line

---

🎬 Unlock the Mind, Unlock the Scene

Ever wondered why some performances hit you right in the gut, while others just float by? It’s not luck — it’s psychology, philosophy, and instinct.

In my course, we go deep into the human mind:

Freud → Understand the hidden drives, inner conflicts, and desires that shape your character.

Jung → Explore archetypes, shadows, and the collective patterns that give your role mythic resonance.

Nietzsche → Learn to embrace struggle, chaos, and life itself, transforming it into raw energy for your performance.

This isn’t abstract theory — it’s practical, on-set knowledge:

Build characters that feel alive, complex, and unforgettable.

Hit the emotional beats instinctively.

Turn tension, darkness, and chaos into performance gold.

Whether you’re in front of the camera or behind it, these tools take your craft to another level.

💥 Your mind is your stage — let’s train it to perform.
LONG VERSION 🌀1 to 1 on ZOOM,intensive,acting workshop.helping to push your emotions to the edge.leading to a powerful "sizzle"reel and possible employment on the 8 features I am shooting this year and next..long version.

Including "river talks"produced by "little pig films"

🌀🎬🎥🌚 Exclusive 1-on-1 Acting Workshop

🔥 Limited-Time Offer – Only a Few Spots Left! 🔥
(📩 Message Now to Secure Yours!)

"Imagine walking into an audition with unshakable confidence, delivering a performance so raw and real that the director can't look away."

This isn’t just another acting class. It’s an intensive experience designed to break barriers and elevate your craft.

---

🎭 What Makes This Course Different?

"This course integrates the poetic realism of Tarkovsky, the practical wisdom of Michael Caine, and the transformative techniques of Stanislavski and Method Acting. Designed to deepen your craft, it focuses on authentic emotional connection and powerful storytelling."

Along with working with, Freud, Yung,and Nietzsche..to understand "subtext and archetypes".

🎬 Created by a British Cinematographer/Director with 31 Years of Experience and 32 Features to His Name

🌍 International Experience: Having worked on films worldwide, collaborating with actors and directors, I bring real-world insights from both sides of the camera. This course is designed to give actors a deep understanding of their craft, emphasizing emotional depth and character development.

📽 IMDb: www.imdb.com/name/nm1806508

📽 Showreel: https://enkiproductions1.8b.io

---

🎬 Exclusive Opportunity – A Direct Path to Real Work!

At the end of the course, each student will create a high-impact “sizzle reel”, showcasing their strongest performance moments.

🔹 This reel will be personally passed on to the directors of the next 7 feature films I am working on as cinematographer.

🔹 That means real exposure—real opportunities—real chances for work.

🎭 "This isn’t just training. This is your shot to be seen by directors actively casting for upcoming projects."

---

🤔 What You Will Learn:

🌀 Emotional Range – Master a full spectrum of emotions for believable, compelling performances.

🌀 Character Development – Create rich, multidimensional characters with depth and 
realism.

🌀 Method Acting – Use personal experiences to deliver raw, authentic performances.

🌀 Working with Directors & Crew – Learn how to hit marks, understand shooting ratios, and collaborate effectively.

🌀 Scene Preparation – Techniques for script interpretation, emotional connection, and performing under pressure.

🌀 Industry Standards – Create a professional showreel and understand how to stand out to casting directors.

---

🎬 These Courses Are One-on-One with the Mentor/Director, Who Will Push You to Make the Performance Believable.

---

🎬 Course Breakdown

Day 1: Moment-to-Moment Acting (Stanislavski’s Approach)

🔹 Breaking a Scene Down: Internal visualization and meditation to "become" the character.

🔹 Character Exercise: The Hitman’s First Kill

📍 Scene: A low-rent hotel room in Manhattan, lit by a dull winter’s midday light. The sad hum of a ceiling fan, distant sirens, muted traffic below. On the bed—a brand-new sniper rifle.(You will be encouraged to "visualize"this)

💥 "Actors I've trained have gone on to land real roles—this course gives you what drama schools miss."

🔹 Exercise 1: Enter the room, pick up the gun, examine it, and prepare for the target.

🔹 Exercise 2: Explore multiple emotional shifts (relief, doubt, fascination, decision).

🌀You have entered the room you are safe (singular emotion)

🌀You see the gun on the bed,the awareness of your reality sinks in.

🌀You make a descion to approach the gun 

🌀You pick up the gun,initially you are captivated by the mastery of it,s creation (momentarily distracting you from the reality of what you are about to do.)

🌀You make the descion to kill(remember in this excercise this is a 1st time "hit person"..why do you make that descion?(Covered in class).

🌀You move to the window,practical ,Now you have decided action will take place.

Explore why using stanislavski techniques,of breaking a scene into ,moment by moment.

It is more fascinating to watch.on screen,the audience does not know "what is going on in your head"..but it is fascinated to watch,and it captures your audience.

🔹 Discussion: How do actors like Heath Ledger, Daniel Day-Lewis, and Dustin Hoffman make their characters so real? Insights from my own experiences on set.

🌀:(monologue)an actor,s ability to memorize lines is important .

🎬:in the style of "the late great heath ledger of "Batman dark knights"(a crazed man sits with a portable nuclear bomb,on his lap):

🌀"So you imagine chaos was created in a day?(Sinister,sarcastic)(Pause/breath)"do you think e equals m squared (slow word by word,as if talking to a child),means we can travel back in time?(Smiles,and cricks his/her neck),no it just means we can build an atom bomb!!,and blow things up!(Smiles and claps hands gleefully),we are all going to die (bows as if on stage),and just by chance we,ll remember why.(Pause)...we even did this?,looks at camera slowly . reflectivity,or just perhaps...mmm I don,t know "nobody cares"!!!!!!.

Lifts button to camera and presses it!!!!..

Boom!!!(Note my last student took the entire session to make this believable).

End scene.🎬🎬

---

Day 2: Making Your Character Believable

🔹 Understanding the Psyche: Whether playing a killer or an ordinary person, you must know your character’s mind.research I had a director friend who contacted "Liam neelson"to understand him
Heath ledger locked himself in a hotel room
The actor from the "machinenist"almost starved himself to death.

🔹 Character Exercise: The Breaking Point

📍 Scene: A crowded supermarket. A tired voice announces deals over the PA. You feel unseen, unheard, frustrated—until suddenly, you’re holding an AK-47. (Scenes can be altered if a student is uncomfortable.)you open fire!!!.

Bang bang bang.
The feeling of power and saying 
F......you all.

Is almost zen like just firing the gun,every round as it falls to the ground is an expression of the rage of anger you feel about ,been born, having to survive,having to make a living,for this day and this day only!(You know for sure the police will kill you)

But this is your day!!!

I will direct you for this scene.

To make it believable

You will have to use "method"and the ability to "source"that"inner rage(which we all have).
To make the scene believable.

Shown to directors I know ..I imagine (if done right,they will be "blown away")

🔹 Alternative Scene: A Joker-like monologue before detonation.

I have script from this scene we can work with.
But it explores "chaos/anarchist"concepts (as expressed by the joker (heath ledger )In "Batman dark knights"

🔹 Alternative Scene: A video call to the person you love most—desperately trying to convince them not to leave.

The point of this scene (if you choose it)is to make your performance totally believable.

🎭 "Imagine the tension of a final phone call—the stakes couldn’t be higher. This is where real acting happens."

🔹 Accents: British, American (Deep South), and Northern Irish accents for performance versatility.

🔹 Final Exercise: The Power of Stillness – convey pure serenity in front of the camera.

The American Indians used to say "a camera steal,s your soul"

A film camera can almost "see inside you"
The purpose of this course is to help you create that "believability"and emotion.

---

Day 3: Working with a Director and Crew

🔹 Understanding your role in the filmmaking process.

🔹 Technical skills: hitting marks, lighting awareness, and camera shooting ratios.
If you don,t appreciate what your crew does,and are say arrogant,well does not make for a nice shoot?

Most actor,s I have worked with are empathetic,kind and understanding 
🔹 Collaborating with crew—continuity, sound, makeup, cinematography, and direction.

📽 Final Showreel Scenes:

🎭 Sinister: "So you really think you got away with it?" You imagine that your karma was not noted,your actions had no consequences.

🎭 Heartbroken: "But I didn’t mean it... please, don’t leave me…I know now that without you I could never imagine how my life would be"

🎭 Insane (Joker-like): "Mmm... if E = mc², then time versus chaos... Means excistance is just a theory ,I have this bomb..the one thing Einstein /Oppenheimer manager to create..so bye bye..let,s push the button!!

🎭 Flat & Emotionless: "We’re born, we live, we die. That’s it." If heaven exists,and we are re.born with "conciseness ",then heaven would become like hell,
As "time"and a sense of time ,knowing we are going one day ,gives us ..in way (deep pause look to camera)a security.

---

Day 4: Fear and Survival – Personal Experience & Character Creation

🔹 Deep Dive: Exploring fear, survival, and desperation in character work.

🔹 Exercise 1: The Jungle Escape
📍 Scene: You’re lost in the jungle at night. Every step is agony, but stopping means death. You call out—pleading for help. No answer.

🎭 Emotions to Explore:

1. Fear of death – the realization that no one is coming.

2. Desperation – the raw instinct to survive.

3. Physical exhaustion – feeling your body give in.

🔹 Exercise 2: The Final Phone Call Redux
📍 Scene: You’re on the phone with a loved one. You need their help. If they refuse, it’s over.

🎭 "This isn’t just acting—it’s about reaching deep into your own experiences to find truth in the performance."

------

🎬:Session 5: Unlocking the Inner World — Freud, Jung, and Nietzsche in Action

 🚨A short script will be given:

🎥:."Sometimes I just can,t feel my self inside,it,s as if something is missing ,but ..I can,t quite put my finger on it"

Jung ,Freud and Nietzsche will be discussed in class...there different philosophies on life .

Perform the script 3 times with those different subtexts in mind.

---

Objective:

To integrate the psychological and philosophical concepts we've explored (Freud's hidden desires, Jung's archetypes, and Nietzsche's self-empowerment) into a character's internal journey, enhancing the depth of performance and pushing actors toward more complex, dynamic roles.

---

🚨1. Understanding the Inner Conflict (Freud)

Exercise:
Guide your actors to explore a hidden desire or repressed emotion within their character that contradicts their outward behavior.
Example: An actor playing a “stoic” hero could uncover a deep fear of abandonment they are trying to repress, which sneaks through in moments of weakness.(Script will be given)

🌀Goal:
Reveal the complexity of a character by exploring subconscious drives and how they create inner conflict in their actions.

---

🚨2. Finding the Archetypes (Jung)

🌀Exercise:
Ask your actors to identify which archetype (Hero, Shadow, Wise Old Man, Rebel, etc.) their character is embodying in the scene.
Then, have them break the archetype — let them experiment with how the character could act outside their usual role to reveal something deeper about their personal growth.(Script will be given)

🌀Goal:
Explore how different archetypes influence a character’s actions and how those archetypes evolve through the story.

---

🚨3. Creating the Übermensch Moment (Nietzsche)

🌀Exercise:
Have your actors play out a moment where their character faces a crucible—a choice that pushes them beyond their old self and forces them to create their own values.
Example: A character might choose self-sacrifice to uphold their personal code, even though it risks everything (script will be given)

Goal:
Challenge the actor to play moments of personal transformation, where their character is creating their own power in the face of destruction or moral ambiguity.

---

🌀4. Integration and Performance

Exercise:
Give your actors a scene where all three elements come into play:

Freud's inner conflict (hidden desires or repressions)

Jung's archetypes (the character wearing multiple masks)

Nietzsche’s self-empowerment (the character breaking free and reimagining their world)
Guide them to play the scene with all these layers, digging into the internal battle, archetypal masks, and the potential for self-transformation.(Script will be given).

Goal:
Combine these psychological and philosophical elements to create a rich, multi-dimensional character.

---

Wrap-Up:

Discuss how each character’s internal journey was shaped by their hidden emotions, their spiritual archetypes, and their search for power.

Reflect on how they can continue to explore their characters’ deeper layers in future roles.

🎬 Final Performance (Day 4):

Students will perform a final emotional scene, bringing together everything they’ve learned. These performances will be recorded as raw material for their showreel.

💥 Their best moments will be compiled into a high-impact sizzle reel—directly sent to directors casting for upcoming feature films.
That I am either producing or about to be cinematographer on.

---

🎬🎥 Ready to Elevate Your Acting?

🔥 For Less Than the Price of a Casting Workshop, You Get 1-on-1 Coaching and a Real Chance for Work!

📢 LIMITED SPOTS AVAILABLE – MESSAGE NOW TO SECURE YOUR PLACE!

📩 DM or Email: mikeenkiproductions1@gmail.com

Let’s create something unforgettable.
---

---

Mike Muschamp’s Philosophy Map – The Big Five

1️⃣ Freud – The Mind’s Hidden Drives

Core idea: Unconscious desires and fears shape behavior.

Use in acting/storytelling: Know why characters (and people) do what they do. Subtle gestures, hesitation, tension = meaningful.

2️⃣ Jung – Archetypes & Shadows

Core idea: Universal patterns, archetypes, and the hidden “shadow” influence life.

Use in acting/storytelling: Tap into archetypes to make characters mythic; explore shadow for emotional depth.

3️⃣ Nietzsche – Will to Power & Self-Overcoming

Core idea: Life is chaos; create your own meaning and values.

Use in acting/storytelling: Turn struggle into strength, show transformation, act boldly.

4️⃣ Camus – Absurdity & Joy in Struggle

Core idea: Life has no inherent meaning; joy comes from living fully despite it.

Use in acting/storytelling: Embrace absurdity in scenes, add existential tension and truth.

5️⃣ Viktor Frankl (“Frank”) – Meaning in Suffering

Core idea: Even in suffering, humans can find purpose; choosing your attitude = freedom.

Use in acting/storytelling: Transform hardship into performance, purpose, and inspiration.

---

How They Mix Together – Your Signature Lens

Freud + Jung: Understand inner drives and archetypal patterns.

Nietzsche + Camus: Embrace chaos, self-overcome, find joy in struggle.

Frank: Give all of it purpose; turn learning and life into meaning.

Result: A philosophical toolkit that powers acting, directing, writing, and living

items.text:
We're seeking an exceptional actor to portray George Harrison in 'A Time To Kill' - our darkly satirical drama exploring the conspiracy surrounding John Lennon's assassination.

The Quiet Beatle speaks. This is a powerful, complex role for an actor ready to bring depth and authenticity to one of music's most iconic figures.

AUDITION DETAILS:

 📅 Friday 24th October 2025 

⏰ 12:00pm - 4:00pm 

📍 @thecasaliverpool Hope Street, Liverpool

 🎭 Playing age: OPEN

TO AUDITION: ✉️ Send CV + recent photo to: howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk 🎤 Prepare 2-3 minute monologue of your choice ⏰ You'll be allocated a specific time slot

PRODUCTION: 🎬 Rehearsals: Week of 3rd November (6 weeks) 🎪 Performances: 8th, 9th & 10th December at CASA

This is an exceptional opportunity to be part of a controversial, compelling new work examining one of music history's most significant events.

We welcome performers of all backgrounds and experience levels.

Ready to bring George Harrison to life?

Apply now: howl.michael1963@yahoo.co.uk

#ATimeToKill #CastingCall #GeorgeHarrison #TheBeatles #LiverpoolTheatre #ActorsWanted #CASA #NewPlay #December2025

casting call 

As a part of a school application I need to shoot a 3 minute bit.

The project will be about the exciting meeting of 2 friends outside of the prison one of them was in for two years.

I’m looking for a male actor who’d be taking the role of the friend who’s being released from jail, ideally mid - late 20’s, dark short hair (if someone here has a buzz cut that would be freakin amazing ) 

It’s a really low budget project but I’d be happy to give a small symbolic payment to a talented actor who’d be engaged in telling our story

items.title: casting call

items.text:
Hello, 
We are looking for two performers to act in a short movie. “Where the Light Shines” explores denial, anxiety, and female identity in a male-dominated society. The film reflects the tension between masculine and feminine energy – control and surrender – and how these forces collide in the face of inner truth.
The story uses contemporary movement and dance to showcase the troubled inner-word of the characters. You will be working closely with the director and choreographer to shape the narrative.
Females, non-binary and all ethnicities is encouraged to apply!<3 This is a third year Bachelor project.  
If you are ready to move with the lights, contact us at: edsh.production@gmail.com.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL - SUPPORTING ROLES FOR “DUALITY: THE SERIES” - LED BY INDEPENDENT FILMMAKERS.**

**DUALITY: THE SERIES** is a 4 part coming of age, teen drama limited series that explores the lives of 4 young adults who are navigating different stages in their lives, in each episode we reveal the internal battles of **1 of the 4 characters **and explore themes of** mental health, growth, identity, family, friendships and more **- they are left to choose between who they want to be vs who they are expected to be. 

We’re looking for more **actors to audition for supporting characters** in our short film series ***Duality: THE SERIES***, based in or around **Manchester**!

**Deadline to submit audition tapes :** 17/11/25 at 23:59

**Note:** This is a **volunteer-based project** for now, but payment, travel, and accommodation **may change** as production continues securing funding.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and collaborate with a passionate and creative team.

If you’re interested in auditioning, please click the link to apply and you should receive your audition pack shortly.

**Filming Location: Manchester, Uk**

**Dates: TBD ( JULY and AUGUST 2026)**

[https://forms.gle/PNTyxuGLKCFeWBv4A](https://forms.gle/PNTyxuGLKCFeWBv4A)

If you have any issues with the link please message me.

Good Luck!

items.text:
Hi, hello, Sat Sri Akaal, I’m Sukhmanjeet, A 16 year old aspiring actor from Australia, who will be taking a giant dive (preferably from a plane) into acting.

it should be clear that I am 16 ALTHOUGH, I have a beard, which by itself sounds very anticlimactic… BUT  🙂‍↕️ it gives me a wider range of characters to portray 😎 (depending on length and gritty-ness) sometimes people mistake me as a 27 year old with my little sister as my child and it’s fun to act that out 😅 fond memories.

I’m roughly 182 cm tall (abt 5’11 3/4), 
weigh 85 (I do plan on becoming fitter and losing weight), 
My Entinicty is south Asian/ Indian (Sikh),
Hair: black and almost shoulder length
Hair-Style: to be a wolf but as of now still growing it out 🤞
Eyes: brown
My chest size is roughly 107 cm and my hips are 97 cm

I decided to take drama classes last year, fell in love, and have focused on many different roles always pushing for roles in different projects, I’ve volunteered to act in student’s film assignments just for the experience. The way I see it, every chance to act is a step closer to getting really good at what I want to do. 😁
 
I’m genuinly so grateful for everyone’s who have been with me, my teachers, my friends, directors and I could not be less excited to meet more amazing people such as yourself, so if your an actor, creator or a director,
Let’s connect and possibly get the chance to make something incredible together‼️

Email: sukh.singh7t@gmail.com
Number: 0421505765
Or you could reach me here on Facebook 😄.

items.text:
Hey filmy friends!!!

Community is a lot like a garden. If you want a healthy, vibrant one, you gotta cultivate that shit. You gotta tend it and care for it. So, let's really dig in and build the most incredible community/garden we possibly can. 

This means ya gotta get off your tuchas and show up. Show up for events and meetings and elections and programs and festivals and screenings and all the hooooo ha. 

You want people to come see your project, ya gotta go see theirs. 
You want people to hire you, ya gotta get out and meet the people hiring. 
You want to find great people to be on your set, then ya gotta get out and meet the people you want to hire. 

Get involved!!! Sign up for shit!! Have fun!!! Make cool stuff!!! 

The next fun thing we have is this Friday. The CFVA is hosting a Halloween party. You can dress up or not, but be there! Show up. Play. Engage. Connect. It's how we will grow CO Film into something undeniable!!!! 

Come find me and say hi. I'll be busting ghosts!

items.text:
Hello Everyone!

My name is Rayonna Price and I am writer/director for a short film called 'Cursed'. It is a University of Colorado Denver film.

A woman suffers through a rough day, will she get through unscathed or will someone lose their head?

Dionne and Jason have been casted for, however, we still are still looking for our Nadine and Bryce. All locations are in central Denver, and our filming dates are November 13th-16th. Transportation can be provided.

To audition and find sides follow the google link here: https://forms.gle/KJJKmE3bG3HgYHkDA

Actors will be reimbursed, please audition we would love to have you apart of production!

Thank you!

**034  Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Szukamy mężczyzn na 30.11.25  ( casting on-line )**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Grupa1940’’** poszukuje mężczyzn jako francuskich cywili uciekających przed atakami niemieckich żołnierzy. Mile widziane osoby z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrza czy Katowic w różnym wieku. Zdjęcia próbne chcemy realizować w Gliwicach.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

**Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

**012  Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Szukamy ojca głównej bohaterki ( casting on-line )**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów ‘’Grupa1940’’ poszukuje mężczyzny do roli ojca głównej bohaterki. Najlepiej jakby kandydat miałby od **40 – 45 lat** o rudych włosach i bez zarostu, o określonych parametrach: **obwód w klatce 100- 105, obwód pasa 90/95 cm** i **wzrost: 175 -180** . Szukamy kogoś **z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice** najdalej. Postać ta będzie nosić mundur polski podporucznika.Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic. Niestety nie zwracamy kosztów podróży. Postać mężczyzny pojawi się w pierwszym odcinku i zostanie zabita przez odział niemiecki. Pojawi się też w retrospekcji bitwy w 1919 roku z Bolszewikami gdzie zostanie ranny w nogę. Oczywiście mile widziane doświadczenie pracy z tekstem. Scenę wstępnie będziemy realizować na przełomie marca lub kwietnia.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. items.text:
KRAKÓW, TEATR NIEZALEŻNY

Szukam ludzi do spektaklu historyczno-poetyckiego, w stylu filmowym, epickim, opartym na życiorysach Tadeusza Borowskiego i Krzysztofa Kamila Baczyńskiego. Premiera przewidziana jest na marzec 2026 roku. Potrzebuję ludzi czujących epokę, poezję, niekoniecznie zawodowców. Poniżej lista postaci, do których szukam aktorów:
* Tadeusz (postać główna, pierwowzór - Tadeusz Borowski i Wincenty Gawron)
* Krzysztof (pierwowzór - K. K. Baczyński)
* Stary Doktor (pierwowzór - Janusz Korczak)
* Kapelan (pierwowzór - ksiądz Tiso)
* Bracia żydowscy Jakub i Izaak
* Roma (żona polskiego oficera)
* Pola (pierwowzór - Barbara Baczyńska)
* ''Święta'' (handlująca zrabowanymi kosztownościami)
* oficerowie hitlerowscy - Wolf i Jurgen

Chętne osoby zapraszam do kontaktu na priv. Pozdrawiam.

sharedPost.text:
Chcesz zostać aktorką/aktorem albo mieć więcej aktorskiej pracy ale nie wiesz co konkretnie zrobić? 🤔 Jeżeli tak - zapraszam na konsultacje do mnie, nagranie wizytówek i montaż demo aktorskiego! 🎬🤩 Szczegóły w opisie! 

🎥 Mentoring aktorski 

Dla kogo? 

Dla każdego kto chce pracować jako aktor/aktorka na planach zdjęciowych. Zarówno dla tych bez doświadczenia, któryórzy nie wiedzą jak zacząć i co zrobić jak i dla tych co już pierwsze kroki mają za sobą ale chcieliby mieć więcej pracy i potrzebują rady w tym zakresie 🙂 

Na czym polega? 

Spotkanie ze mną 1:1 online, trwające godzinę. Opowiesz mi jakie zlecenia aktorskie Cię interesują - czyli Twój aktorski cel i według tego dobieramy odpowiedni plan działania. Jeżeli masz materiały aktorskie - to je omówimy i powiem co warto byłoby jeszcze do nich dodać lub jak je “podrasować”. Jeżeli nie masz to dowiesz się co i jak masz zrobić żeby je mieć 🙂 Powiem o moich poleceniach agencji aktorskich, jak samodzielnie i łatwo zrobić demo, jak nagrać i co powiedzieć w wizytówkach, jak samodzielnie szukać pracy, jak się wyceniać, na co uważać. I odpowiem na wszystkie inne Twoje pytania. Po spotkaniu otrzymasz ode mnie maila z planem działania i priorytetami do wykonania + materiałami pomocniczymi dot. materiałów aktorskich. 

🎥 Coaching aktorski z wizytówki + nagranie wizytówek w studio 

Na czym polega? 

✅ Tworzę tekst do wizytówek na podstawie informacji o Twoim doświadczeniu, pasjach, zainteresowaniach, który dostajesz przed nagraniem według castingowych wytycznych, który pokaże Twoje największe atuty

✅W studio nagrań nagrywamy 3-4 wizytówki:

🎬 do filmów i seriali 
🎬 do reklam w wersji dłuższej 
🎬 do reklam w wersji krótszej 
🎬 w języku obcym 
Ewentualnie możemy dograć wizytówkę modelingową 

✅ W trakcie nagrywania zadbam o Twoje rozluźnienie, dobrą atmosferę oraz zrobimy kilka ćwiczeń które pomogą pokazać na wizytówkach Twoją energię i błysk w oku 
oraz będę czuwać nad całym procesem

✅ Wizytówki nagramy według aktualnych standardów i wymogów castingowych 

✅ Dostaniesz zmontowane wizytówki gotowe do wysłania przez WeTransfer

🎥 Demo aktorskie 

montaż demo aktorskiego + konsultacja 

Na czym polega? 

✅ otrzymasz ode mnie demo aktorskie zmontowane zgodnie z obecnymi wymogami reżyserów castingu + podczas konsultacji wspólnie dobierzemy sceny, które się w nim znajdą oraz przedstawię Ci mój pomysł na ich kolejność 

Podczas konsultacji dowiesz się również:

✅ jak pobierać materiały do demo aktorskiego 
✅ jakie są obecne wymogi i standardy wzgledem aktorskiego demo 
✅ jakie sceny wybierać i w jakiej kolejności je zmontować  
✅ jak samemu w łatwy sposób przemontować demo pod konkretny casting 

Szczegóły priv

items.text:
Til min kortfilm Banana Ice, der er støttet af Odense Filmværksted, søger jeg to kvindelige spillere til venindeparret Rikke og Sika - spillealder 19-20.

Banana Ice handler om:

Den 18-årige Val, der i starten af historien får nedtur på efter hun, ved ankomst til baren, finder ud af at hendes veninder har ditchet hende. 

Men det bliver faktisk bare held-i-uheld, for hun ender med en aften på bar med venindeduoen Rikke og Sika.

Da de to veninder, sent på aftenen, går ud for at spice øllene op og narkopolitiet kort efter kommer ind, ender Val i et dilemma.

Hun redder hendes “nye” veninders røv, men i panik og for at redde deres egen røv, kaster Sika og Rikke hende under bussen.

Kortfilmen hedder som den gør, fordi en vape, med den smag, er gennemgående motif i historien.

Praktisk:

Kortfilmen optages i Svendborg den 29. og 30. november i dagstimerne - så der er selvfølgelig forplejning. 

Er du og måske din veninde interesseret?

Så send en mail til majamus23@gmail.com med emnet Venindeduo_BananaIce

I mailen kunne jeg godt tænke mig:

* en video af dig/jer, der som de to veninder skal få den sidste ved bordet til at købe drikkevarer til jer - det kan f.eks. være via en løgn, en leg, at stjæle eller noget helt andet.

* har du/I en showreel eller links til andet I har lavet, så send det gerne med.

* en kort, kort præsentation af dig/jer.

Her kommer lidt om veninderne:

Rikke&Sika

Sammen er de den uovervindelige venindeduo.

Man ved, ser man den ene et sted, så er den anden lige om hjørnet.

De er det kvindelige modsvar til det heteroseksuelle forholds tosomhed.

Noget både jeg og Val er misundelige på.

De er spændende og fascinerende mennesker, man ønsker at dele en aften med.

 

Sika

Hendes forældre er succesfulde, så hun kommer fra et hjem hvor der bliver forventet noget af en.

Kærligheden er ikke ubetinget, man skal præstere og gøre sig umage, før man får et klap på skulderen eller en belønning.

 

At være uartig eller opfører sig dårligt fører naturligvis til konsekvenser.

Sika finder nydelse i at være meget langt fra sine forældre, men hjemmet har klart givet hende en hårdhed.

 

Rikke

Hun har en enlig mor, inden hende og Sika blev en tosomhed, var Rikke og hendes mor det.

Hun trives godt i det kvindelige selskab og elsker fællesskab og andre menneskers samvær. Derfor former hun sig også meget efter de mennesker hun er sammen med, så hun altid passer ind og kan være en del af de sociale.

Til min kortfilm Banana Ice, der er støttet af Odense Filmværksted, søger jeg to kvindelige spillere til venindeparret Rikke og Sika - spillealder 19-20.

Banana Ice handler om:

Den 18-årige Val, der i starten af historien får nedtur på efter hun, ved ankomst til baren, finder ud af at hendes veninder har ditchet hende. 

Men det bliver faktisk bare held-i-uheld, for hun ender med en aften på bar med venindeduoen Rikke og Sika.

Da de to veninder, sent på aftenen, går ud for at spice øllene op og narkopolitiet kort efter kommer ind, ender Val i et dilemma.

Hun redder hendes “nye” veninders røv, men i panik og for at redde deres egen røv, kaster Sika og Rikke hende under bussen.

Kortfilmen hedder som den gør, fordi en vape, med den smag, er gennemgående motif i historien.

Praktisk:

Kortfilmen optages i Svendborg den 29. og 30. november i dagstimerne - så der er selvfølgelig forplejning. 

Er du og måske din veninde interesseret?

Så send en mail til majamus23@gmail.com med emnet Venindeduo_BananaIce

I mailen kunne jeg godt tænke mig:

* en video af dig/jer, der som de to veninder skal få den sidste ved bordet til at købe drikkevarer til jer - det kan f.eks. være via en løgn, en leg, at stjæle eller noget helt andet.

* har du/I en showreel eller links til andet I har lavet, så send det gerne med.

* en kort, kort præsentation af dig/jer.

Her kommer lidt om veninderne:

Rikke&Sika

Sammen er de den uovervindelige venindeduo.

Man ved, ser man den ene et sted, så er den anden lige om hjørnet.

De er det kvindelige modsvar til det heteroseksuelle forholds tosomhed.

Noget både jeg og Val er misundelige på.

De er spændende og fascinerende mennesker, man ønsker at dele en aften med.

 

Sika

Hendes forældre er succesfulde, så hun kommer fra et hjem hvor der bliver forventet noget af en.

Kærligheden er ikke ubetinget, man skal præstere og gøre sig umage, før man får et klap på skulderen eller en belønning.

 

At være uartig eller opfører sig dårligt fører naturligvis til konsekvenser.

Sika finder nydelse i at være meget langt fra sine forældre, men hjemmet har klart givet hende en hårdhed.

 

Rikke

Hun har en enlig mor, inden hende og Sika blev en tosomhed, var Rikke og hendes mor det.

Hun trives godt i det kvindelige selskab og elsker fællesskab og andre menneskers samvær. Derfor former hun sig også meget efter de mennesker hun er sammen med, så hun altid passer ind og kan være en del af de sociale.

Glæder mig til at se jeres mails <33

Kh Maja, manus/instruktør

Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran and I’m currently working on my first short mobile horror film. The script is in progress, and I’m looking for passionate people who would like to join me on this creative journey.

I’m specifically looking for:
🎬 A professional film editor
🎥 A camera operator (based in Durban/Chatsworth area)

The goal is to work together as a team and create something special. This project isn’t about making money — it’s about sharing stories and giving audiences an enjoyable and memorable film experience.

If you’re interested in being part of this project or know someone who might be, please feel free to reach out. Let’s build something amazing together!

From 
KM PICTURE

items.text:
Due to the amount of interest and questions. 

Playing age is not important, ideally it’s being filmed as a recount in 2010, but equally it can be set in 2025. 

The original working outline script has been posted on my own Facebook bio to give a better idea of the shoot. If I can I’ll add it to this page too. 

I’ve been invited to submit a script I wrote as a short film in a festival. It’s a true story told by the girlfriend of a mob boss from 1980’s

You’ll be recounting your time from a Sloane Ranger to a mob girlfriend in a “London penthouse” in the main as dark shots/reflections of close up body parts (assumed naked). Talking to a mirror with red lipstick (a bit generic)

It’s a 15 min short I’ve got a hotel giving us 3 days of use of an apartment but it’s self funded so we are budget conscious. 

You’d need to commit to your own dress dress/hire and travel for the IMDB event in London but we will rent a hotel suite. 

I’d cover travel and expenses to film in Cornwall. 

Probably 3 of us sharing a sleeps 6 holiday apartment. Additional fee is negotiable on your ability.

Sok szeretettel várlak a XI. kerületben, a Fehérvári út 168–178/A alatt (1116 Budapest), ahol gyönyörű, tartós és személyre szabott pillákkal varázsolom még különlegesebbé a megjelenésed 😊🫵

🎄 A karácsonyi időszak közeledik, és a helyek rohamosan fogynak, úgyhogy ha szeretnél tökéletes pillákat az ünnepekre, ne hagyd az utolsó percre a foglalást!

💌 Időpontért írj üzenetet, és gondoskodjunk együtt arról, hogy csillogj az ünnepek alatt is 💫

Munkáim/árlista:

topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. You can't tell me there isn't money out there for Christian films. I guarantee the parishioners could put in some money for the film when the collection plate is passed around. How many Christian churches are within 50 miles of you? I bet there 2 dozen and probably more. You can't tell me there aren't at least 10 people at each church who couldn't put in $10 each. 

You can also start a crowdfunding campaign, get a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes at various churches, meet with local businesses for product placement. 

All those churches weren't built for free. I guarantee you all those who built the buildings were paid for their services so the churches can sure help pay for a Christian based film. 

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

PAYING PEOPLE...IT'S WHAT JESUS WOULD DO!

items.text:
Hello fellow NYC actors and filmmakers! 

My name is Eunji, an actor, filmmaker and founder of Dreama. My company is opening a new workshop for actors, DREAMA ACTING LAB 💜

This is going to be very special and transformative experience as an actors and artists to develop your acting skills to another and deeper level.

The registration is now OPEN and you can submit this google form below:
https://forms.gle/ofW1Yu2MhihCvfV68

Can't wait to see you beautiful & talented actors in the same room together for this new journey! 

Hugs,

Eunji Lim

sharedPost.text:
🪻[DREAMA ACTING LAB] in Fall - Winter 2025🔬

Hello dear DREAMA Family & Friends 😇
Dreama is proudly opening a new acting workshop!

📍About DREAMA ACTING LAB
Dreama Acting Lab is opened for Actors and people who want to learn acting from Method Acting to Dreama Method created by Eunji Lim, our artistic director.
For actors, you will develop the ability to tap into your deeper self, train your awareness, imagination and creativity by learning about your instrument with sensitivity and vulnerability. Through our abundant techniques, you will amplify your stage presence and discover how to co-exist with others through breath, while refining your body, mind, and soul to craft yourself in order to meet your character at the “intersection.”

🪄HOW TO REGISTER
Submit Google Form (Link below)
🔗https://forms.gle/ofW1Yu2MhihCvfV68

🪄 REGISTRATION DUE DATE
Until November 5th (Wed)

🪄 SCHEDULE
November 10th — December 29th
Mondays, 6 pm - 9 pm

🪄 LOCATION:
Studio in Manhattan
(TBA for Registered Students)

🪄 For Whom:
- Actors who hope to develop their acting techniques and create their own method
- Actors who want to take their craft to the next level
- Actors who want to refine their awareness and imagination to be fully present on stage
- Actors who want to fully embody their character and connect deeply with co-actors on stage
- Actors who love learning and exploring Method acting

📧INQUIRY
dreamaworkshop@gmail.com

We will look forward to meeting new actors and artists for our new journey together! 🚢❤️

Hope you shine as you always do ✋🏻✨🤚🏻

Let’s Dreama!

items.text:
CASTING CALL – Student film CCA "love"

Union Status: None Union 
Location: CCA lowry campus 
Production Type: Short Film
Genre: comedy/romance 
Filming Dates: November 7th
Compensation: Meals, Footage

ABOUT THE PROJECT

Its about BLAIRs first day of being a couples councilor. Her first appointment is with a couple CHRIS and JACKIE and they are there for Chris's addiction that overwhelmed Blair.

SEEKING THE FOLLOWING ROLES

Blair – Female 23, just received her master's degree to be a couples therapist and its her first day.

Chris – Male 27, Active duty military, about to get deployed soon married to Jackie

Jackie - Female 24, headstrong, preppy.

SUBMISSION INSTRUCTIONS
Please send the following to dwmadero11b@gmail.com
Headshot
Resume or reel (if available) 
Role(s) you are submitting for
Availability for NOV 7th
Subject line: Love – [Role Name] Submission

OPEN CASTING CALL

Rose Waite Studio are looking for inter-generational pairs who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. You will get the chance to watch a live theatre show from the opera box at one of Lloyd Webber’s theatres.

You could be a grandparent and grandchild, friends or colleagues etc. who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. 

You’ll need to be based in or near London. 

This is a paid opportunity. 

If you’d like to be filmed sharing your story, email stories@rosewaite.com with details of your story together and why theatre matters to you both.

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Thank you!

items.text:
**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP  Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )  **

 

   Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć.  Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 30 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania,  na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Temat 1 – ‘’Kobieta mafii 1930’’**

Postać kobiety osadzona w 1930 roku w roli bogatej kobiety, która trudni się gangsterstwem. Przewidziane są ujęcia m.in. przy stoliku na którym są pieniądze, wino, rewolwer. Tło jest wydrukowane w formie muru, cegieł. Motyw sensualny.

 

**Temat 2 – ‘’Wampirzyca w baroku 1700’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana najpierw w suknie czarną oraz peleryne z kapturem. Do tego czarna długa peruka oraz czarne paznokcie. W kolejnym etapie sesji motyw sensualny.

 

https://www.maxmodels.pl/lukus_wielki2

**Zapraszam na stronę Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

sharedPost.text: Pomimo swojego ogromnego majątku wynoszącego 400 milionów dolarów, Keanu Reeves jest bardzo skromny i prowadzi życie zwykłego człowieka. 🤷‍♂️💰 Preferuje proste przyjemności, takie jak kawa i kanapki, często widywany w miejscach publicznych, gdzie miesza się z normalnymi ludźmi. Fani nawet nazywają go „niezłamanym”. 😳🤫 Dlaczego woli proste życie od luksusu i bogactwa? Odpowiedź jest bardzo prosta... 😮➡️ Sprawdź więcej zdjęć w komentarzach poniżej 👇👇👇

# Improvised Filmmaking Workshop in Berlin
## One week to go!

Actors & Directors: Ready to create powerful scenes spontaneously? ✨

Explore the magic of actor-director collaboration in our **Improvised Filmmaking Workshop**.

This hands-on weekend intensive is for all levels. We’ll explore the creation of compelling stories together, building trust, and finding freedom in your craft.

## 🗓️ **UPCOMING DATES:**
* Nov 1/2: **Only three spots left**
* Nov 15/16
* Dec 6/7

## **THE LOWDOWN:**

🎬 For Actors & Directors (all levels)

🇬🇧  In English

⏰ Sat & Sun, 10:00 – 19:00

📍 Reflektor Neukölln

Read what past participants have to say: reviews available on my website!

Don't miss out.

#FilmmakingWorkshop #ActorWorkshop #DirectorWorkshop #ImprovisedFilmmaking #BerlinCreatives #BerlinFilm #BerlinActors #BerlinDirectors #Neukölln #ReflektorNeukölln #WorkshopBerlin #IndieFilmmaking #Improv #SceneStudy #Collaboration

We're currently casting an international actor (age 25–36) for the main role of a short film shooting between November 2–3 in Warsaw.

The story is a black comedy about David, an immigrant spending his first christmas in another country with his girlfriend's family. 

❗️Requirements: Must know another language than polish and english, must communicate well in english aswell.

This is a non-profit project, but catering and transport are provided, along with a valuable creative experience in audiovisual storytelling.

If you're interested or know someone who might be, feel free to message me for more details. Looking forward to collaborating! 

🫶🏻For contact my email is : ikateon7@gmail.com

Been cooking up a lot of projects behind the scenes and this is the most recent! 

Currently casting for a new short, working title 'The Heist', filming in Northern Quarter, Manchester!

In 1994, a duo of thieves, interrogated after a heist gone wrong, find their fates decided by the value of their mysterious stolen item 🪙

STUDENT FILM, SHOOTING IN MANCHESTER, EARLY NOV, UNPAID

THE INTERROGATOR

mid 30s. 

Stoic but becomes fascinated with the two thieves' stories. 

RAY

20 - 30

Confident, in charge and narcissistic. Takes the lead within the duo

NICK

18 - 25

new to the crime world, scruffy and erratic. Intimidated by Ray.

Within plenty of space to collaborate, build and bring your own energy and flair to the story and the characters, this may be a good opportunity for upcoming actors building their portfolio and looking for experience! 

We are currently looking for self tape auditions

If interested please message me here or email izzyhambury1@gmail.com

for further details

We now have classes in the area . Hollywood acting classes right on your doorstep. 

Led by an Internationally award winning actor and coach. 

Check the post below and contact us if you are an actor or ever dreamt of being one. 

The only Spotlight and SAG acting studio in the whole U.K.

sharedPost.text:
⭐ The Questions Every Actor Asks ⭐ (Answered Honestly)

You’ve got questions ⁉️ 
We’ve got answers.
And we’ve built our entire school around them.

Q: How do I know your school is legit?
Because Spotlight the UK’s official professional acting authority reviewed our curriculum and we exceeded their approval by more than three times.
Because we’re also SAG Recognised the same union that represents every major Hollywood actor in the world.
No other independent school in the UK can say that.

Q: Why would I pick you over any other school?
Because other schools say “Spotlight approved” but then hand out the same generic scripts week after week, rush performances, and give zero feedback.
We don’t.
Our curriculum changes every week. It’s structured, focused, and personal. Every actor gets individual coaching not a cookie-cutter session.

Q: Will I actually get anywhere with this?
Yes. Because our actors do.
We make real films 
short and feature length, shot on professional RED and ARRI cameras.
Our students act in those films, gain IMDb credits, build real showreels, and appear in festivals. As well as getting cast in films all over the country. 
That’s not a claim, that’s proof.

Q: Is this another acting scam?
No. We don’t take tier payments, we don’t upsell, and we don’t run an agency that locks you in.
Every actor pays the same, no matter their level.
We believe in fairness, transparency, and results.

Q: What makes your coaching different?
You’ll be trained directly by an internationally trained coach who has studied across the UK, Ireland, and the USA, not part-time tutor reading from a book.
Our coach doesn’t just teach what to do, he teaches  how the industry actually works.

Q: What about the issues I’ve had before…. unorganised classes, lazy feedback, cliques, rude online behaviour, and coaches that put actors down ?
We fixed all of that.
Our curriculum is consistent, our feedback is personal, our students are professional, and our reviews prove it.
You won’t find drama in our drama school, only growth.

Q: Will I get an agent or auditions?
We don’t own an agency (because that’s a conflict of interest).
But we do help you find one, a real one.
We train you to audition, self-tape, and present yourself like a professional actor, not a hopeful amateur.

So why us?
Because every complaint actors have ever made about acting schools, we’ve fixed it.
And because every question you’re asking right now, we’ve already answered with action.

🎭 SPOTLIGHT APPROVED • SAG RECOGNISED • FILM FOCUSED
🎥 Real coaching. Real results. Real films.
👉 Message us to join your free induction class across Yorkshire & the North.

casting call 🚨

As a part of a school application I need to shoot a 3 minute bit.

The project will be about the exciting meeting of 2 friends outside of the prison one of them was in for two years.

I’m looking for a male actor who’d be taking the role of the friend who’s being released from jail, ideally mid - late 20’s, dark short hair (if someone here has a buzz cut that would be freakin amazing 😭) 

It’s a really low budget project but I’d be happy to give a small symbolic payment to a talented actor who’d be engaged in telling our story 💗

I’m looking for a male actor who’d be taking the role of the friend who’s being released from jail, ideally mid - late 20’s, dark short hair (if someone here has a buzz cut that would be freakin amazing 😭) 

It’s a really low budget project but I’d be happy to give a small symbolic payment to a talented actor who’d be engaged in telling our story 💗

CYCLIST CASTING

Hello, I'm a local film director here in Vancouver and we are casting for an exciting reveal video for a cycling World Tour team (road cycling).

We are in search of a body-double for a rider due to some scheduling nuances. 

Seeking: Female presenting, brown hair. 

Shooting Location: Vancouver

Dates: November 12th (possible fitting on November 10th) 

Compensation: $300 CAD 

No acting experience necessary, but looking for someone who looks great on a bike! 

If interested please EMAIL to hello@dorodango.ca : 

-casual photo of yourself in cycling kit 

-height

-video of you riding a road bike on a turbo trainer 

-a little blurb about your cycling/racing experience

Please email all submissions to hello@dorodango.ca , facebook messages will NOT be checked.

items.text:
CASTING CALL 

Evolo Productions is now casting for our next feature film, Mnemonic! 

**Synopsis**

As an unexplained anomaly throws the world into chaos, Chantelle, a scientist, believes that one man may hold the key to fix everything. 

**Production Company: **Evolo Productions

**Producer(s): **Valen Elbeyli, Kate Obbagy, Zachary Obbagy

**Director: **Zachary Obbagy

**Casting Director: **Kate Obbagy

**Union Status: **Non-Union

**Project Type:** Ultra Low Budget Feature Film 

**Rehearsal Date**

February 8th 2026 

**Shoot Dates**

February 12th - March 1st 2026 

**Shoot Locations**

Vancouver, North Vancouver, Burnaby, Northern BC 

**Compensation**

$170 CAD per 8 hour day - Number of days varies by character. 

**Additional Info/Safety Protocols**

Shoot includes travel and potential extreme cold weather.

All flights, stay and food will be covered for shoot in Northern BC.

Crew members will be trained on heat/cold safety. Daily safety meetings will be held to maintain compliance. Warming stations and weather appropriate clothing will be provided. 

**Submission Details**

Deadline - November 14 2025

You can Submit your audition through our Website, https://www.evoloproductions.com/audition or directly via email.

In your submission, please include your name, character name, headshot / reel to Auditions@Evoloproductions.com to receive sides. Self-tape auditions will be accepted via a Google Drive link or WeTransfer. Preferred titling: Character_FullName_Date

Top candidates will be asked to join us for an in-person callback on December 7th. 

**Chantelle**

**Age: **Mid to late 30s

**Gender:** Female

**Description: ***Lead - Chantelle is one of the few remaining scientists still working on finding a solution to the anomalies terrorizing the world. Though her work isolates her, there is a quiet warmth beneath her guarded exterior. She balances determination with vulnerability that emerges in rare moments, making her both a voice of reason and a reminder of what's at stake. *

**Aaron**

**Age: **Mid to late 30s

**Gender:** Male

**Description: ***Co-lead -**** ****Aaron has been living a simple life in isolation, in a remote town far from the big city and his past reputation. Unbeknownst to him, he is in possession of something that will change things forever. Aaron has to make a choice; continue to hide from his past or dare to remember it, knowing the memory itself can destroy him or finally set him free. *

**Ryan**

**Age: **Mid to late 30s

**Gender:** Male

**Description: ***Supporting - A paramedic hardened by years on the job, Ryan has lost faith in humanity's worth. He still saves lives but out of duty rather than belief - driven by muscle memory instead of hope.*

*When Aaron brings him on a mission to save the world, he must decide whether to keep action out of duty or rediscover a reason to believe. *

**Captain Henry Stacey**

**Age: **Late 40s to early 60s

**Gender:** Male

**Description: ***Supporting - Captain Stacey has been in the police force for most of his adult life. He is authoritative and uses his position and rank for personal interest. Stacey is the hero of his own story and isn't afraid to take matters into his own hands if he feels things are going wrong.*

attachments.ocrText: Kan være et billede af tekst, der siger "STATISTER SOGES Vi soger statister til at spille politibetjente uden replikker til en spillefilm produceret af PIGS UNITE Optagelse: mandag d. 27. oktober (mulig option torsdag d. 30. oktober) Location: Veerlose Tidspunkt: Forvent et tidsrum mellem 7：00-17：00 7：00- 7:00 Vi soger 4 statister alderen 25-45 Honorar: 500DKK Er du interesseret? Sả send en mail til GKIK.Statistkordinator@hotmail.com Dit Navn Alder Et nyere foto (portreet) Tlf. nr. Skriv gerne om bade du kan mandag d. 27. oktober og torsdag d. 30. Vi haber at hore fra dig"

items.text:
Genre: Romance/Drama

Logline: Soulmates bound from the beginning of time must navigate the blurred lines between dreams and reality to discover their destiny together.

Roles:

Atlas: 20s, Male

Atlas always feels the weight of the world on his shoulders. He understands more about life and the universe than most people, which doesn’t help his abilities to strike up a conversation and ends up making him look reserved and detached. Atlas feels everything from the rotation of the Earth to everything that is supposed to happen in the future. His connection with the world makes him patient, almost seeming like he is unable to act on his desires, because he knows what the future holds.

Luna: 20s, Female

Luna enjoys the complexities of figuring out what life is. She wants to follow her passions and figure out what they mean along the way. She isn’t the type to turn people away, but instead see what they change in her life. She is never afraid, takes her own mortality in her hands, and believes there is a right answer to everything. The spark of life is in her and she doesn’t want to let anything snuff it out. Her dreams start to show her the past and what the future holds for her.

Pierce: 20s, Male

Pierce is a constant. He is dating Luna. He never does anything unexpected. He has a very simplistic view of the world and events that occur outside of it don’t really concern him. He is steadfast in his decisions and never doubts who he is or what he is doing. You can always expect him to be around, but if things get deeper he will very quickly drown from the weight of his inexperience.

Production Company: pearscarfproductions

Writer/Director: Nathan Chelf

Cinematographer: Nate Coberly

Production Type: Independant

Contact Info: pearscarfproductions@gmail.com

Run Time: Short Film

Compensation: Negotiable, this is a low budget, self funded project.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: We will be holding in person auditions this Saturday, October 25th from 9:00 AM until 2:00 PM at 3111 E Colfax Ave Denver, CO 80206. Please email us if you are interested and we will get you a time slot. If you are unable to make it in person please reach out and we will set up a virtual audition another time or send you information to do a self tape. For in person we would love to see a monologue and we will have you do cold readings from the script.

Shooting Schedule: We are planning to be filming in December, final dates will be confirmed based on the schedules of our cast.

Filming Locations: The Denver Metro Area

Thank you for taking the time to read through this and I hope to hear from you soon!

items.text:
CASTING CALL FOR A STUDENT SHORT-FILM!

Hi hi! My name is Megan Veto and I am a student at the Aurora Community College and will serve as the Writer/Director of this project. I am in need of actors/actresses for my Production 1 project! This will be unpaid, though I will provide anyone interested with a final version of the film. You will also be fed, so please let me know of any allergies or specific diets you may have!

Title: On the Rocks
Genre: Romantic Comedy
Logline: An angry bride walks into a bar and shakes up Ramos’s day.

SHOOTING DAYS: November 8th (10a - 6p) - 9th (1p - 7p)

LOCATION: 9075 E Lowry Blvd Denver, CO 80230

CHARACTERS:

-Ramos: The bartender. Late 20’s - early 30’s. Calm, cool, and collected. Takes care of his patrons. Wardrobe will be all black and a black button-up shirt.

-Sarah: The angry bride. Mid - late 20’s. Feisty, knows what she wants, but eventually softens under Ramos’s care. Please let me know what your dress size is so I can find a bride’s dress that fits! 😁

-Mike: The ex. Mid - 20’s. Flustered, desperately looking for Sarah. Cheated. Wardrobe will be black slacks and a nice white button-down shirt.

-Ruth: Sarah’s mom. 50’s. Helps Mike look for Sarah. Wardrobe will be a nice dress.

Please email me at megveto96@gmail.com with your headshot and demo reel, I will send you the script to read over.

Thank you so muc

items.text:
Hello , my name is Slavi and Iam à Movie Producer 

I just created a new International  film Platform for Professionels (Directors , Producers , Distribution company …. ).  If you have a Feature Film or a Short Film you can submit and your Movie will be watched in country like America , Australia , Europe , Asia or even Africa . 

Every 10 weeks we will host Film Festivals  in different cities such as London , Stockholm , Berlin , Madrid , New York , LA ….  And showcase the best movies . 

So if you already have a Feature or Short film and you want to be part of this Festival and the international platform 

Text me really quick 
Send me a message and will book à call . 

Have a good day 
Slavi .

items.text:
Want to learn how to transition from doing music into Acting?
Or how to get your music in TV and Film? 

BBR Indie Films is thrilled to announce our Celebrity Guest  Panelist- Gary "LIL G" Jenkins! 

​Gary "LIL G" is a National Platinum Recording Artist (lead singer of the R&B super-group SILK), Producer, Songwriter, and Actor.

​His impressive acting credits include:
🎬 Madea's Family Reunion (Stage Play)
🎬 Sleepy Hollow
🎬 Christmas Bae (coming soon)

​Don't miss the chance to hear from a true industry veteran at our next event, we are giving all the tea. Come ready to network, we ALWAYS have several Music Supervisors in the house.

​📅 Wed, October 29th, 2025
📍 Studio Movie Grill - Marietta, GA
⏱️ 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM
👻 In the theme of Halloween. Costumes are welcomed but not required. Best Costume wins a prize. 

​Secure your tickets and learn more about BBR Indie Films at bbrindiefilms.com and on Eventbrite!

sharedPost.text:
✨ A Smile for Christmas – A song that brings warmth and a smile.
When the world outside is wrapped in snow, the pan flute tells of that special moment when a simple smile means more than any gift.
Gentle tones that touch the heart – a musical light in the quiet, festive season.

A song that reminds us: Christmas doesn’t begin under the tree, but in a sincere smile. 🎄😊

A Smile for Christmas – Ein Lied, das Wärme und ein lächeln schenkt.
Wenn draußen die Welt in Schnee gehüllt ist, erzählt die Panflöte von jenem besonderen Moment, in dem ein einfaches Lächeln mehr bedeutet als jedes Geschenk.
Sanfte Klänge, die das Herz berühren – ein musikalisches Licht in der stillen, festlichen Zeit.

Ein Song, der daran erinnert: Weihnachten beginnt nicht unter dem Baum, sondern in einem ehrlichen Lächeln. 🎄😊

Composer : Pan Hope (Horst Peter Zoll)
Artist : PAN HOPE #musik #christmastime #newmusic

**Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Szukamy aktora żandarmeria polowa (casting – on-line)**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów **‘’Morskie opowieści’’** poszukuje mężczyzny do roli szeregowego niemieckiego żandarmerii polowej. Żołnierz ten wystąpi w dwóch  odcinkach 2 i 3 odcinku podczas zatrzymania kobiety, jednej z kluczowych postaci. Tekst będzie po niemiecku. Przewidujemy wcześniej kilka sesji testowych. Bardzo ważnymi czynnikami będą parametry kandydata: **obwód w klatce 90 –95 cmwzrost 170 – 175 obraz pas 85 –90 cm. **Szukamy kogoś **z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice** najdalej. Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic. Niestety nie zwracamy kosztów podróży. Postać mężczyzny pojawi się w pierwszym odcinku i zostanie zabita przez odział niemiecki. Oczywiście mile widziane doświadczenie pracy z tekstem.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

**Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane’s resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could’ve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a “Karen Carpenter” fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

items.text:
**CASTING CALL – Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s–80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional — a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film’s psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40–85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control — much of the horror relies on stillness and presence

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s–80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional — a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film’s psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40–85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control — much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Have you ever wanted to be an actor ? 

Many schools around teach only theatre 🎭. We are a film and television only internationally recognised acting studio. 

All actors in the U.K. dream of becoming spotlight performers and we are spotlight approved. All actors also dream of working in Hollywood and we are also the only acting studio in the U.K. that’s also SAG recognised. 

All actors want to work on films , or what’s the point training to be an actor ??? 

Well we make that happen and right on your doorstep. 

Message us now for all times , locations and prices . We are also the cheapest in the country for such a high standard curriculum. 

Look forward to having you in class and seeing you on set.

items.text:
🎬 **CASTING CALL – COVENTRY UNIVERSITY FINAL YEAR FILM** 🎬

We’re currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations — confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

📅 **Filming Period:** Mid-February to March 2026
🎞️ **Length:** Approx. 15 minutes
🎭 **Genre:** Horror Comedy

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We’re looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you’re interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I’ll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We’re aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you’re available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! 🎥✨

items.text:
· Title: This Side of Midnight

· Genre: Horror

· Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

· Role: Lilith — Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera — Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith’s best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad — Male, 40s–50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom — Female, 40s–50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling — Any gender (preferably male), 10–15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier — Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

· Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin — Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange — Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

· Production Type: Student Film

· Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange — escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

· Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

· Compensation: Unpaid

· Union Status: Non-Union

· Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1–2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

· Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

· Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

· Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one’s own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

items.text:
Für meinen No-Budget-Kurzfilm „Stella“ suche ich engagierte Schauspieler:innen aus der Umgebung von Nordhorn.

Catering, Showreelmaterial und eine familiäre, leidenschaftliche Drehatmosphäre sind selbstverständlich vorhanden.

Unterkunft und Gage können leider nicht übernommen werden.

Kurzbeschreibung des Films:

„Stella“ erzählt die Geschichte einer jungen Frau, die seit Jahren versucht, ihrem Bruder Felix aus der Patsche zu helfen – koste es, was es wolle.

Als Felix in ernste Geldsorgen gerät, überschreitet Stella Grenzen, um ihn zu retten. Doch als sie Nick kennenlernt, prallen Loyalität und Liebe aufeinander – und alles droht zu eskalieren.

Ein emotionales Drama über Verantwortung, Geschwisterliebe und das Loslassen.

🪞 Kurzbeschreibung des Films:

„Stella“ erzählt die Geschichte einer jungen Frau, die seit Jahren versucht, ihrem Bruder Felix aus der Patsche zu helfen – koste es, was es wolle.

Als Felix in ernste Geldsorgen gerät, überschreitet Stella Grenzen, um ihn zu retten. Doch als sie Nick kennenlernt, prallen Loyalität und Liebe aufeinander – und alles droht zu eskalieren.

Ein emotionales Drama über Verantwortung, Geschwisterliebe und das Loslassen.

⸻

🎭 Gesuchte Rollen:

🔹 Felix (ca. 20–25 Jahre)

– Boxkenntnisse oder Grundfitness erwünscht

– Ruhiger, leicht muskulöser Typ

– Stelllas Bruder, gerät in finanzielle Schwierigkeiten

🔹 Jan (ca. 20–25 Jahre)

– Bester Freund von Felix

– Ebenfalls sportlich / Boxerfahrung von Vorteil

🔹 Kleiner Felix (ca. 6 Jahre)

– Für Rückblenden

– Verspielt, offen, gerne erste Kameraerfahrung

🔹 Mutter von Stella (ca. 30–35 Jahre)

– Für Rückblenden

– Warmherzig, sympathisch 

🔹 Boxer / Trainingsgegner (20–30 Jahre)

– Kurzer Auftritt in Trainingsszenen

– Sportlich, authentische Boxbewegungen

⸻

📍 Drehort: Nordhorn 

🎥 Drehzeitraum: Jan/Feb

💡 Art: No-Budget-Projekt (Catering & Showreel inklusive)

– Warmherzig, sympathisch 

🔹 Boxer / Trainingsgegner (20–30 Jahre)

– Kurzer Auftritt in Trainingsszenen

– Sportlich, authentische Boxbewegungen

⸻

📍 Drehort: Nordhorn 

🎥 Drehzeitraum: Jan/Feb

💡 Art: No-Budget-Projekt (Catering & Showreel inklusive)

items.text:
🎬 **Filmprojekt sucht weibliche Darstellerinnen (Raum München)**

Für ein unabhängiges Fan-/Action-Filmprojekt im Stil von *Assassin’s Creed*, *COD* und Fantasy-Elementen suchen wir noch **motivierte Darstellerinnen** für verschiedene Szenen.
📍 Drehort: Raum München / Grafing

👗 Kostüme & Requisiten werden gestellt
🎥 Erfahrung ist kein Muss – wichtig sind **Teamgeist, Zuverlässigkeit und Spaß am Spielen vor der Kamera**

Bei Interesse einfach kurz per PN melden – ich sende gern nähere Infos zum Projekt.
